title: Historic Jamestowne Part of Colonial National Historical Park: Women Preserving Jamestown
body: "To Preserve and Protect" Two Women Making a Difference at Jamestown       Although all of the first 104 settlers landing on Jamestown Island were men, women played an important role in the history here, too, both in colonial days and in more recent times. Meet two women whose skills in preservation, organization and interpretation helped create and maintain the legacy we enjoy today here at Jamestown. Please click on the names below to learn more about each woman.                 Ellen Matthews Bagby             Virginia Sutton Harrington
